Peter Okoye of PSquare has announced only those with Permanent Voter Cards(PVCs) can visit him at home and office. The angry music star, who joined several celebrities to condemn the horrific Owo attack that claimed many lives, via his Twitter handle on Monday reechoed the importance of individuals securing their PVCs ahead of 2023 elections. He said he has duly instructed his security and management not to allow anyone into his home or office except they show their PVC.   FFK’s estranged wife glad to reunite with kids     Owo terror attack: May Nigeria not happen to us – RMD     Polygamy will solve marital infidelity, says Arike Gold   The 40-year-old singer tweeted: “I have just instructed my security and my management that No one is allowed to visit my house or my office without showing there PVC! “This also includes my management team and entourage! No PVC! No Visits and Travels!… We must get it right this time and vote out bad leaders.”